Sex = {'Male': 0, 'Female': 1}
Salary = {'<=50K': 0, '>50K': 1}

data['sex'].replace(Sex, inplace=True)
data['salary'].replace(Salary, inplace=True)
data['race'] = data['race'].astype('category')
data['relationship'] = data['relationship'].astype('category')
data['marital-status'] = data['marital-status'].astype('category')
data['occupation'] = data['occupation'].astype('category')
data['education'] = data['education'].astype('category')
data['occupation'] = data['occupation'].astype('category')
data['native-country'] = data['native-country'].astype('category')
data['workclass'] = data['workclass'].astype('category')
cat_columns = data.select_dtypes(['category']).columns
cat_columns
data[cat_columns] = data[cat_columns].apply(lambda x: x.cat.codes)

8- calculate mean using for loop:

In [410]:
start_loop = time.time()


def forLoopMean():
    sum = 0
    count = 0
    for index, row in data.iterrows():
        if row['education'] == 9:
            sum += row['hours-per-week']
            count += 1
    return sum / count

print('mean : ', forLoopMean())
end_loop = time.time()

mean :  42.546669366268475

As you can see vectoziation is too much faster:

data_copy['salary'] = data['salary']
data_copy.hist(figsize=(15, 15), legend=True);

def calc_Mean_Std(data_):
    return data_.mean(numeric_only=True), data_.std(numeric_only=True)
More50 = data_copy.loc[data_copy.salary == 1].drop('salary', axis=1)
more50_mean, more50_std = calc_Mean_Std(More50)
less50 = data_copy.loc[data_copy.salary == 0].drop('salary', axis=1)
less50_mean, less50_std = calc_Mean_Std(less50)

data_map = pd.DataFrame({
    '>50K_Mean': more50_mean,
    '>50k_Std': more50_std,
    '<=50k_Mean': less50_mean,
    '<=50k_Std': less50_std
})

features_cnt = data_map.shape[0]

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=features_cnt, figsize=(15, 30))
fig.tight_layout(pad=5.0)

x = np.arange(-5, 5, 0.01)

ax_index = 0
for index, row in data_map.iterrows():
    axes[ax_index].plot(
        x,
        stats.norm.pdf(
            x, loc=row['>50K_Mean'], scale=row['>50k_Std']
        ),
        label='>50K',
        color='cornflowerblue'
    )
    axes[ax_index].scatter(
        More50[row.name],
        stats.norm.pdf(
            More50[row.name],
            loc=row['>50K_Mean'],
            scale=row['>50k_Std']
        ),
        color='royalblue'
    )

    axes[ax_index].plot(
        x,
        stats.norm.pdf(
            x, loc=row['<=50k_Mean'], scale=row['<=50k_Std']
        ),
        label='<=50k',
        color='red'
    )
    axes[ax_index].scatter(
        less50[row.name],
        stats.norm.pdf(
            less50[row.name],
            loc=row['<=50k_Mean'],
            scale=row['<=50k_Std']
        ),
        color='firebrick'
    )

    axes[ax_index].set_title(row.name)
    axes[ax_index].legend()
    ax_index += 1
